owl:Ontology.terms:title: Ocean Protein Portal Ontology
owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment: An ontology for describing data types used by the Ocean Protein Portal
owl:Ontology.rdfs:label: Ocean Protein Portal Ontology

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Aggregates means that the domain DataType is a new DataType that requires at least one instance of the aggregates range.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: aggregates

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The defining Parameter is an annotation of the target Parameter
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: annotationOf

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies that a Dataset meets the criteria for a certain DataType.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: dataType

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: This parameter depends on the existence on another parameter.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: dependsOn

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Extends means that the domain DataType is a specialization of the range DataType by inheriting the range's Parameters but also incluing new Parameters as part of the specialization.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: extends

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: This inferred parameter stores the value of the parameter in range.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: inferredParameter

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies that a DataType should include the associated Parameter.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: measures

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies that a DataType recommends that the associated Parameter be present, but does not require it.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: recommends

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies that a DataType must include the associated Parameter.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: requires

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: This parameter is narrower version of its range. It a specialization of its range by because of some detail such as a specific unit of measure or becuase it was observed using a specific instrument.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: specializationOf

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies that the SubjectArea pertains to the observations made for a DataType.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: subjectArea

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The value of this Parameter is the summation of Parameters attached by this property.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: summationOf

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: For parameters whose data value is a list of multiple values, this property defines a string that determines how that value should be parsed into a list of values by specifying the string identifying where the value should be split.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: delimiter

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A string, indicating a format for the data value that enables correct processing of the value. For example, a date value may have a format such as 'YYYY-MM-DD'. Since the a format specified here are implementation specific, this definition does not enforce any particular range on this property.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: dataValueFormat

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A data type can include more meaning beyond the syntax, such as who created the data type, the source standard that the data type derives from, the operations that can be done on datasets of that data type, and typical scientific domains, software programs and/or instruments that use the data type, etc. The intent is that any humans or machines that when they encounter that data type can quickly 'understand' or be in a situation to at least 'process' details within the dataset without even downloading that dataset.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DataType

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An inferred parameter is a parameter whoa value is not explicitly recorded in the Dataset, but that can be inferred based on its data type and related metadata. For example, dataset collected on a Cruise might not explicitly record the cruise in the dataset, but that it can be inferred through the metadata: (odo:Dataset -> odo:fromDeployment [ dc:title ]).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: InferredParamter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A certain field of study used to group or filter Data Types
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SubjectArea
